  <!-- Tractor Trailer Training -->
  <item>
    <title>Tractor Trailer Training</title>
    <link>http://tricountydrivingacademy.com/courses/tractor-trailer-training/</link>
    <pubDate>Thu, 01 Jan 2015 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
    <dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
    <content:encoded><![CDATA[
<p>The trucking industry is experiencing driver shortages and companies are looking for well trained drivers.</p>
<p>Graduates will have the knowledge and skills to become Class "A" CDL licensed drivers qualified to drive long distances, regionally or locally.</p>
<h3>Program Details</h3>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Program Length:</strong> 4 weeks</li>
  <li><strong>Schedule:</strong> Classes start monthly</li>
  <li><strong>Price:</strong> $3,800 (includes tuition &amp; books)</li>
</ul>
<h3>What You Will Learn</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Pre-trip inspection procedures</li>
  <li>Basic vehicle control and backing maneuvers</li>
  <li>Shifting and braking techniques</li>
  <li>Coupling/uncoupling procedures</li>
  <li>Hours of service regulations</li>
  <li>CDL written and skills test preparation</li>
</ul>
<p>Upon completion, graduates receive a certificate of completion and are prepared to obtain their Class A CDL license. Students may also receive 12 college credits from Southwest Virginia Community College or Mountain Empire Community College.</p>
    ]]></content:encoded>
